9:21 AM Defendant Arturo Guyo Rosales in court, in custody from ACJ.  Attorney Daniel Francis Snyder in court for Arturo Guyo Rosales.  Attorney Ruth Diane Kressel in court for State of Wisconsin.  Cases 21CM32, 22CF174, 22CF48, 21CF147, and 21CF34.  Papers just filed in cases this morning, taking pleas.  Parties have agreement with pleas.  Court is more than likely going to order a PSI.  Atty and def leave court room to discuss.  Back on the record at 9:36.  Atty indicated to go forward with plea hearing and ordering of PSI.  State has complied with victim rights.  Def understand charges and range of potential penalties.  Atty def agrees that he is a repeater.  Atty def admits that he is a domestic abuse repeater.  Def agrees to both.  22CF174 recv'd copy of complaint, waives reading.  Waives right to prelim hearing.  Def agrees, understands rights giving up. 
 Atty is satisfied.  Court is satisfied and accepts WOPH.  Court has reviewed complaint, finds PC that a crime has been committed case is bound over.  State is filing information now.  Atty waives reading.  Atty, def pleads NO CONTEST, def agrees.  Files contain PLQ, def understands information, rights giving up, and elements.  Back on the record at 9;59.  Court printed out information and clerk gave to Atty and def.  Back on the record at 10:09.  Atty is satisfied.  Court is satisfied and accepts pleas.  As a factual basis can court rely on information in the complaints, parties agree.  Court finds a factual basis exists, finds def guilty and direct judgment to enter.  Court orders a PSI for all cases.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 6, 2023 at 01:00 pm.
